#### ❌ MEM-1: `pendingEvaluations` Map grows unbounded — no eviction

**File:** `src/self-evolution.ts` — lines ~185–200
**Code:**
```typescript
private pendingEvaluations: Map<string, Promise<LLMEvaluationResult>> = new Map();

// scoreCandidateAsync:
const evalPromise = this.evaluateWithLLM(content);
this.pendingEvaluations.set(memoKey, evalPromise);
try {
  const evaluation = await evalPromise;
  return this.createCandidate(content, index, evaluation, skill);
} finally {
  this.pendingEvaluations.delete(memoKey);  // ← only deleted on success path
}
```
**Problem:** The `.delete()` is inside the `finally` block, but if any exception escapes between `set` and `delete` — including synchronous throws in `createCandidate` — the entry **remains forever**. On any evaluation failure (network timeout, Honcho crash), the Map grows. With high-volume evolution runs (`evolveAllSkills` → parallel over N skills), this is a guaranteed memory leak under failure conditions.

**Fix:**
```typescript
private pendingEvaluations: Map<string, Promise<LLMEvaluationResult>> = new Map();

// scoreCandidateAsync:
const evalPromise = this.evaluateWithLLM(content);
const memoKey = `${skill.slug}:${index}:${content.substring(0, 50)}`;
this.pendingEvaluations.set(memoKey, evalPromise);
try {
  const evaluation = await evalPromise;
  return this.createCandidate(content, index, evaluation, skill);
} catch (err) {
  throw err; // rethrow after cleanup
} finally {
  this.pendingEvaluations.delete(memoKey);  // now always cleaned
}
```

