#### ⚠️ WARN-2: `_writeCountToday` resets at midnight but `_lastWriteHash` persists

**File:** `src/honcho-client.ts` — lines ~175–185
**Code:**
```typescript
private _checkAndRecordWrite(content: string): boolean {
  const today = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);
  if (this._writeCountDate !== today) {
    this._writeCountDate = today;
    this._writeCountToday = 0;
    // _lastWriteHash is NOT reset here
  }
  const hash = content.slice(0, 200)...;
  if (hash === this._lastWriteHash) { ... }  // ← stale hash from yesterday!
```
**Problem:** If a server crosses midnight with content X written before midnight, `_lastWriteHash` retains that hash. After midnight, the daily counter resets but the hash persists. If content X is written again on the new day, it will be **incorrectly flagged as a duplicate** and skipped.

**Fix:**
```typescript
if (this._writeCountDate !== today) {
  this._writeCountDate = today;
  this._writeCountToday = 0;
  this._lastWriteHash = '';  // reset hash alongside counter
}
```

